in Hinduism, Durga (Sanskrit:  Durga, meaning "the inaccessible"[1] or "the invincible";Bengali:  durga) or Maa Durga (Bengali: ma durga, meaning "Mother Durga") "one who can redeem in situations of utmost distress"[citation needed] is a form of Devi, the supremely radiant goddess, depicted as having ten arms, riding a lion or a tiger, carrying weapons and a lotus flower, maintaining a meditative smile, and practicing mudras, or symbolic hand gestures.[citation needed] The name is made of Sanskrit dus- = "with difficulty" and similar (compare Greek δυσ- (dys-)) and ga ("come", "go")), with the usual sandhi of -sbefore a voiced consonant.
An embodiment of creative feminine force (Shakti), Durga exists in a state of svatantrya(independence from the universe and anything/anybody else, i.e., self-sufficiency) and fierce compassion. Kali is considered by Hindus to be an aspect of Durga. She is thus considered the fiercer, demon-fighting form of Shiva's wife, goddess Parvati. Product name: Indoor Play for Kids, Family Game Night Fun, Preschool Kids Active Movement, Kids Inside Play, Kids Gymnastics, OT Therapy, PT Therapy Kids
Description:
Indoor Active Play for Kids
Do you have kids that need to work out their wiggles?
Of course you do! 
The Wiggle Box provides a creative (and secretly educational) way for your child to work out all of those wiggles that are trying to escape.  
Choose several coins from the box, put them in a sequence…and, start moving!  The Wiggle Box will have your child doing all sorts of crazy movements that cover both fine & gross motor skills along with a little balance & flexibility, memorization, and more.
Change the sequence and do it all again…and, again. As many times as it takes to work out all of your child’s wiggles! Slow it down, speed it up…the possibilities are endless.
The best part is that the movements never get old...kids can do them over and over again and have a different experience every time!
Here are just a few of the movements you will find in the box:
•Pretend you’re a boxer. Box fast, then slow, then crazy.
•Shrug your shoulders 10 times
•Crawl like a bear. Go over furniture & onto beds.
•Somersault from one end of the room the other
•Wrinkle your forehead & nose. Try to wiggle ears.
•Make your fingers dance. Will it be a slow dance or a fast dance?
   …..and, many more!
Have fun, feel good and give in to the wiggles!
AGES: 3-10
ACTIVITIES: 80 Fun, Wiggly Movements
COINS: 40 natural, wood coins, each measuring 1 ½ inches round
BOX SIZE: 4x4x2
NOT for children under 3 yrs. of age.

Description:
▪This listing is for 1 (one) silver plated locket, 1 chain and a complimentary fill kit
▪Please read the listing details and view the listing photos. 
I do have a few solid silver lockets like this in a separate listing  under "Sterling Silver."
▪This SILVER PLATED pendant measures approximately 1" tall & 1/2" at it's widest point. 
▪Included is a very small corked glass orb
So Unique, delicate & ornate~ One of my most popular little lockets. Affordable and pretty. 
▪Choose Antiqued Silver Tone OR Silver Tone locket
▪(Silver tone) is the lighter locket
▪(Antiqued) is the darker locket
▪Chain choices:
1mm 925 silver filled wave 
(This is a very delicate chain, very thin and lightweight)
1mm 925 silver filled o-link (pictured on silver locket)
1mm stainless steel olink  (pictured on antiqued locket)
1mm silver plated ball chain
1mm stainless steel ball chain
These lockets are coated in a clear thin layer of uv protectant acrylic to help preserve the silver plate. Clean only with water and a soft cloth. Do not buff.
▪Read to the bottom for locket care and filling tips.
▪Gold tone and Bronze tone lockets in this style are in seperate listings 
Do no buff and only gently wipe with water on a soft cloth to keep it looking nice. Buffing will wear off the  silver plate. 
LOCKET CARE:
▪Having trouble feeding the chain through the top of the pendant? Simply feed some thread through the loop on the chain, then feed the thread through the top of the locket and pull the chain through. 
▪Your locket will arrive with the glass orb inside. Simply remove the chain to open the locket.
▪Because this orb is so small, the funnel will not fit inside the orb. It will set on top of the orb over the hole. You will need someone to hold the orb while you fill it. Personally, I fold a piece of paper in half and let the ashes slide down the crease into the orb. This seems to be more efficient for this orb size.
▪Dip the tip of the cork in clear glue or clear polish to create a permanant seal. When placing the orb back in the locket, make sure it sets with the cork "up" towards the top of the locket. Do not force the locket closed. If the orb is placed in correctly, it will not require force to close it. If you force it,  it may break. So handle it with care.
▪Orb replacements are sold in my shop in the Fillable Lockets section. 
Please do not hesitate to contact me with any questions. I'm happy to help.
Thank you for viewing my shop. I know that you have many choices.  
SILVER CARE:
Silver plated or solid silver tarnishes at some point. It is important to keep your silver jewelry clean and "DRY." If you live in humid locations, it may tarnish more quickly. Do not wear your silver in the shower or swimming. Store your silver in an air tight bag, such as the one provided with your pendant, when its not being worn. Use a silver cleaner or cleaning cloth ON THE CHAIN ONLY  if it does tarnish. Do not use it on the locket that has been treated. I use TarnX Jewelry cleaner. One quick 'dip" and its back to its natural luster. Only clean the lockets that are coated in acrylic with water on a damp cloth
